76561197987083150,Not Recommended,216910,17931424,"Posted: 7 September, 2015",all,ChibiNyan,"I'll first say this game is quite nice. The art is good, the characters too (playing an orc and a goblin in an RPG with humans as enemies is really refreshing), the story is average but the characters are interesting. However, this game has one serious flaw : frustration.First, all map are linear. More linear than Skyrim's dungeons. More linear than FFXIII's. And all optionnal quests' maps are designed the same way : a linear corridor with 3 battles. Ok, optionnal quests are, you guessed it, optionnal. But in difficulty 3 out of 4, you have to do thoses quests to level up.The battle system is really frustrating. At least in difficulty 3 out of 4 (thus, 4 too, and maybe 2). Especially for those who want a little RP and want a badass orc without hacking through the levels in a too easy difficulty.First, your orc is weak. Well, he's stronger than the average enemy, but I was shocked how quickly he can fall, even in defensive mod. For most battles, you want him in full tank/defensive mode while the little goblin does all the dps...So much epicness is lost here. It would have been better to have the goblin in full status inflicting/assassin role. But no, he will often deal most of the dps...The rage thing is probably the most frustrating for RP players like me. IF Arkain becomes enrage too early, the battle is probably lost. The only moment when the rage is handy, is when there are only one or two enemies left with little HP, and Arkain can benefit from the extra health he gains when he becomes enraged.So, basically, either the rate comes too early and you lose, either it comes too late and you lack the epicness, either it comes in a stupidly easy fight you would have won without touching your controller/keyboard anyway...Why play an orc if you can't go full berserk more often ? Why can't they be a little more useful ?For the battles, the orc is slow. Ok, it's an orc. The muscular beast who hits hard but is slow. However, his attacks can be cancelled by the enemies a bit too easily. And by ""a bit"", I mean ""a lot"". In the early game, trying to stun an opponent fails 3 times out of 4. And the stun time is so short you'll regret trying to stun them. Other skills are so long (because the orc hits multiple times in the same skill), you lose time because he hits the ground after he killed his target... while other enemies are still hitting him in melee range.Those may seems like little details for you. If it is, well, buy the game. I think I said the main problems I encountered with this game. But for those who wanted to play a badass orc, either don't buy it or play in easy difficulty (with all the boredom it may imply)."
