76561197971663658,Recommended,216910,18392999,"Posted: 9 October, 2015",all,alkemmy,"Only just gets the thumbs up.  Looks like yet another action-RPG mass-produced from a basic stencil, just with the graphic set adjusted and a few changes made to menus and such like (here the production company uses the in-house Silk engine instead of UnrealEngine3, but from appearances both are very similar).  There are a lot of them about and almost none has anything to lift it above the others.  This one just pips the entry-level competition to the post by virtue of the character Styx, a slightly cynical wise guy who has seen it all.  He has his own game, Styx Master of Shadows, which is really quite good, possibly better than this one because it draws you in, and this one doesn't have a lot going for it in that department.  The storyline appears to be pretty basic.  It relies a lot on keeping you wondering if it's going to get any better.  I'll add another comment if that does in fact prove to be the case.  But don't wait up, so far it's been a dreary string of learning-curve chores and irrelevent mini-tasks instead of a Hero's Quest."
