76561198094112770,Recommended,216910,35471668,Posted: 4 October,all,ThaiBoyTrader,"This is not a hack-and-slash, fast-paced combat game. So anyone looking for that type of action or enemies that drop pools of loot, I suggest looking elsewhere. It is a game that involves a mild amount of strategy with a good enough story to play through once. The combat is fairly simple, I highly recommend assigning all of your skills to hotkeys, so you don't have to pause the game every five seconds to add a new attack to each character. If  you do this, the game goes by much faster and feels more organic. Personally, I found Styx to be the much more interesting character to play as (go figure, he's the one with the series after the game). Styx adds another dimension to the game with a simple stealth dynamic that makes the actual combat easier.This game does what it aims to do well. However, this is the style of game that is very easy to just find one strategy and use it the whole game (e.g. using Ark as a meat shield, and Styx picks everyone else off on at a time and revives him when necessary). The game is very linear, so don't expect open-world, but it is easy to find the objective and complete it without getting lost or wasting time traveling. The choices in the game are interesting enough to make you contemplate them for a short while. But, once more, the take-home is the story and the development of the characters. Which was the sole reason I continued the game.Overall: 6/10Worth a single play through for fans of the genre onlyBuy on Steam Sale only"
