,Not Recommended,216910,8776893,"Posted: 19 January, 2014",all,Arkan01d,"I've had Of Orcs And Men on my wishlist since it's release. The premise sounded very interesting and the idea of playing as an Orc for once made it even better. However, I held off on purchasing the game. I know Focus does not always release the best of games and I usually give them some time to get all the bugs and stuff under control before I purchase any of their titles. I also saw the critic scores that were just mediocre, but I don't always agree with critics.I said all that to say I have been waiting to play this game for quite a while now and was eager and convienced I would enjoy it. The story is pretty good. The dialouge options are really nice. It's great to hear your character actually say your dialouge choices instead of the silent avatar syndrome. Combat is meh. It's exactly the same as Game of Thrones. It's a mix of real-time/Turn-based combat that has you switching your attention between controlled characters. The problem I have with combat in Of Orcs And Men is the same problem I had in Game of Thrones. All encounters seem to have a slim margin of victory. You will focus on one characters attacks and after issuing 2 or 3 skills, you'll notice the other character is about to die. I don't understand how both of my characters seem to always be near death everytime I change focus. As well the skills you choose in combat aren't all that varied and I found myself sticking to a one two punch combo with my Orc and leaving the goblin as fodder since he's worthless in combat.Combat can be forgive though. I don't mind a challenge as long as the story is good. The reason I do not recommend Of Orcs And Men is FOV!!! That's right! The field of view for this game has to be about 30. Your Orc takes up 45% of the screen. If you choose to switch to the Goblin you're presented with a super zoomed in view. The graphics are great, the set pieces are nice, why they chose to make the view so damn limited and not show off their work defies logic. Game of Thrones had the same issue, but there was a work around. This game has none. It feels like you're trying to play a game while wearing your creepy uncle's coke bottle glasses. I got so dizzy that, after only 1 hour of play I had to stop. I felt like I was going to throw up. Even 30 minutes after playing the game I still feel slightly dizzy. Of Orcs And Men has to worst FOV I have ever experienced in a game.  I doubt I will ever play another Focus release again."
