,Recommended,216910,14535938,"Posted: 18 February, 2015",all,Rae,"Overall, I think this game is worth playing, more for the story than the gameplay. If you're no huge orc fan (I'm not) grab it on a sale at £10 (50%) or so, if you're an orc lover, the full £20 is probably worth it to you.Good:Story is pretty good and well told, even though it's not particularly original.The main characters and more important side characters are well voiced.The graphics in the environment are good, the main characters are very good (Aside some nasty clipping on cloth)It's relatively long for a linear game, I didn't mess around too much and ended up clocking about 13 hours (Including deaths and retries, probably 10 hours)The main characters themselves are very good. They interact frequently, they have a pretty well told backstory and a few surprises to discover later in the game. There are a good few funny moments too. (Of the dark humour kind)The way shopping works is pretty neat. Instead of cash, anything you own has a certain value in barter points (Very few, like, 3 or 4 for a good chest piece) and each thing can be upgraded a single time. You can sell for the points and keep them like you would cash, but you won't earn any. (you can find a few in chests through the game)The music isn't particularly energetic or ringtone-memorable, but it fits the situation very well the entire time. Personally I liked it a lot.Neutral:The game is very linear. You get some choices here and there but they don't make all that much difference. There are some decent sidequests.The rpg elements are ok, but you'll end up just dumping most of the points into 2 stats for each character and using two or three skills on each. You get to upgrade each skill once, with 2 choices for each, which is decent.Bad:The combat seems like a good idea but ends up being pretty boring and annoyingly difficult. I ended up dropping it to easy at about the halfway point because it just became boring and you die ridiculously easily, though it has to be said it can feel rather cool to have ark tank everyone while styx deals with the rest one by one in order of threat. (tip, take out the rangers first, they won't target ark often, they stay out of range of his taunt)The stealth mechanics are too easily foiled by dogs simply detecting you, and at other times you can kill enemies who literally look around in your direction, but don't see you unless they move to completely face you.The general enemies and less important characters look pretty bad. Humans particularly."
