76561198055269636,Recommended,216910,31099935,Posted: 12 April,all,Ron,"A really well made game, solid, it appears like an RPG, but indeed it is NOT, it's mostly a fight game with heavy elements of Real Time mechanics, where you'll be able to freeze the scene and assign the desired movements while in the fight.You'll control an Orc and a Goblin who will cooperate and fight together.The story is really well made, the dialogue lines are crude and mature and the goblin is really funny for his macabre sense of humor.If played at Easy difficulty this game could even be interesting and pleasant but, if played at extreme, the max difficulty level, then this game shows his worse aspect, because it becomes almost unplayable, even hostile toward the player.The game starts very cruel and with no mercy for the player, at beginning you'll be forced to fight since the beginning against 5 or more opponents together and you'll not have  any important survival skills that you'll acquire later, so, remain alive, at beginning, is much harder than in  the middle of the game, when you will acquire important survival skills that will make your journey a little better.A game not for everyone but that could give you some satisfactions if you not aim too high.If i should judge the game as if played on extreme only i would probably give a 75% but i will judge it as if played at easy difficulty, soMy Final Score is80/100"
