,Not Recommended,216910,29530985,Posted: 27 January,all,BOT Heinrich Kramer,"+ characters animation+ storytelling is the best part of the game+ tactical pause and strategy-based battle+ awesome sound designPlaying the game which shares core idea of games as new cinema was a lot of fun, it feels through great storytelling and well animated real-time rendered cinematics followed by touching music, even somehow satisfying epic battles; at this moment you might forgive frustraiting linearity of gameplay and level design failures..BUT WHAT I CAN'T FORGIVE IS ABSENCE OF LINUX PORT!!SHAME ON YOU FOCUS! Also there are some little moment:- some levels are unfinished if you look closer at level design- missions are too linear, there is only one or two paths for styx- there are mostly no verticality in game, except spots for archers- stealth made ridiculous, also game not allow you been pure stealth- there is no coop, but it just must be in such a game- there are no puzzles, lost opportunity of team work"
76561197964863427,Recommended,216910,34957380,Posted: 14 September,all,Kamamura,"I must say I was pleasantly surprised by this game. It offers relatively fresh adaptation of the popular ""noble savage"" trope, with interesting setting, well written dialogues (although the poor translation hinders it somewhat), ambitious scale and immersive atmosphere.On the other hand, everything else is very crude as if the game was programmed by orcs themselves. The combat is absolute unintuitive mess, the equipment system confusing, the stats are hard to work with, sometimes you don't know what to upgrade before you spend resources to see the resulting stats, and if you build your characters wrong, you can face difficult to unplayable battles later in the game.I recommend the game for the obvious ambition of its creators, for their effort to break the monotony of the standard gaming loop with new elements, and for their attempt to create a memorable gaming experience. They succeeded only partially, but not for the lack of effort."
76561197980156403,Recommended,216910,35030214,Posted: 17 September,all,Csta,"Kind of a half-baked game, but the story and setting are both pretty good. Love the voice-acting and dialogue too. Good music. Overall, a pretty decent game. I love any game starring Styx. And Arkail is a convincing and formidable antihero as well. The gameplay in this game can be a little unbalanced and chaotic (I found myself switching between medium, hard, and extreme a lot just to keep myself at the appropriate challenge level throughout the game), but it's still fun enough to keep you going through the story. 8/10"
,Not Recommended,216910,35510376,Posted: 5 October,all,HumanWreckage,"Of Orcs and Men is a complete game that ran well with no crashes for me.  For me the games cons outweigh the pros and I would not recommend this one.  Things like unskippable cutscenes, unavoidable attacks right after cutscenes, limited gear and skill options, and an unchangeable camera that felt zoomed in way too much.About the only real fun I had was stealth killing with Styxx."
